Frank's Spicy Hot Chicken

Ingredients
6.0 Ounce(s): Green Beans
2.0 Unit(s): Scallions
4.0 Tablespoon(s): Sour Cream
7.2 Gram(s): Frank's Red Hot Seasoning
0.25 Cup(s): Panko Breadcrumbs
0.25 Cup(s): Monterey Cheese
10.0 Ounces(s): Chicken Cutlets
12.0 Ounce(s): Yukon Gold Potatoes
2.0 Teaspoon(s): Honey

Instructions
Step 1: Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 Degrees. Wash and dry all produce
Step 2: Trim and thinly slice scallions, separating whites from greens.
Step 3: In a small bowl combine half the sour cream (you will use the rest later), 1/2tsp of the Red Hot Seasoning, and a large pinch of salt. Stir in water 1tsp at a time until the mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.
Step 4: Place 1 TBSP butter in a medium bowl, microwave until melted.
Step 5: Stir in panko, Monterey Jack, and remaining Frank's Red Hot to the bowl. Salt and Pepper to taste.
Step 6: Dice potatoes into 1/2 inch pieces. Place in a medium pot with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil, cook until tender. 15-20 Minutes. Reserve a 1/2 cup potato water, then drain.
Step 7 Add a drizzle of oil and scallion whites to empty pot over low heat, cook until soft 1 minute.
Step 8: Return potatoes to pot, mash with remaining sour cream and 1 TBSP butter until smooth and creamy. Add splashes of potato water as needed. Season with salt and pepper for taste.
Step 9: While Potatoes cook pat chicken dry with paper towels and season all over with salt and pepper. Place on one side of a lightly oiled baking sheet.
Step 10: Mound tops of chicken with panko mixture. Press firmly to adhere.
Step 11: Toss green beans on opposite side of sheet from chicken with a large drizzle of olive oil, salt and pepper.
Step 12: Roast on top rack until chicken is golden brown and beans are cooked through. 15-18 Minutes
Step 13: Transfer green beans to a bowl and toss with 1 TBSP of butter until melted.
Step 14: Divide green beans, potatoes, and chickens between plates. Drizzle chicken with creamy buffalo sauce and honey. Garnish potatoes and chicken with scallion greens and serve.
